<p>13 April 1918<br/>Saturday<br/>A very Cool Change after bright warm weather. In the evening R.S.M. Smith &amp; I went into Salisbury We went to see a couple of Shows which were fairly good &amp; altogether had a fairly good time.</p>
<p>1918 April 14<br/>Sunday<br/>2 after Easter</p>
<p>Same old Stuff In the afternoon Smith &amp; I went into Dinton a very small village on the South Western Line. Had tea there &amp; afterward went to Church (C.E) in a quaint old Church a mile or so out of the town. A number of the boys who have died at Fovant Hospital are buried in the Church yard.</p>
